Zoe take 2

As some of you might remember, I rescued this beautiful brindled girl from a miserable life in a cage at the end of April. I worked with her and a trainer for six weeks, acclimating her to life outside a cage, and she did great- she wasn’t without her issues- counter surfing in particular, and not the best listener, but she improved. A lovely couple adopted her and after a week she took a container off the counter, the wife went to take it from her and she bit the wife- classic resource guarding. So they sent her back. 

I continued working with her, she also spent time with another foster and then I connected with a highly recommend trainer in North Carolina. 

Since being with him she has become a completely different dog- no counter surfing, super good listener, much more at ease. He has been amazing for her and believes she is now ready for her forever family.  She is goofy, very smart, and a good listener. 

Her ideal home would have older children or no children, probably no other dogs, and lots of outdoor time. 

She is currently in North Carolina. 

Dm me if you are interested.

This is the first time in as long as I can remember that I do not feel the promise of a new year. Instead, my heart is aching at the suffering we have witnessed over the past 90 days in Gaza. Not only are innocent civilians being targeted, murdered and maimed, so are all living creatures. Day after day my heart breaks over and over again. As someone who treasures all living things, the environmental cost on top of immeasurable human suffering is profound and unbearable. This space has generally been one of beauty, inspiration and humor. Now all I see is startling cruelty and suffering.

I, like so many others, watched in horror as abhorrent brutality unfolded on October 7th. For days afterwards Israel had the good will off the world which was promptly squandered with its outsized response. 

What we are seeing now, and have been seeing day after day is beyond comprehension. Israel is not “defending”itself, Israel is committing genocide. And in so doing, is simultaneously making all Jews around the world less safe. Half my family is Jewish. If I lived in Germany and it was the 1940’s I would be carted off to the concentration camps with the rest of my family. That said, I reject the slaughter that Israel is committing as it is antithetical to every thing that I hold dear. For those of you who refuse to find compassion and who desperately cling to the idea that one side is evil and one side is good, I encourage you to wake up. Never in the history of ever has an eye for an eye solved anything. Only endless, endless generational trauma and pain. 

As I wonder how to move forward, I reflect on the words of my dear friend Behida @behidadolic for solace. 

“To me, being called an artist is the greatest honor, and a name that comes with tremendous responsibility. Art is a brave personal act, something one human does that creates change in another. Speak up for the thousands of innocent children whose voices are suffocating beneath the concrete. Paint, draw, write, march, share, and demonstrate! The time has come for all of us, regardless of which side we’re on, to put our personal agenda aside and come together for the greater good of humanity.”

🙏🙏🙏
